Additionally, the paper discusses recognizable tree languages, which are a type of formal language, and finite state tree transformations, which are a type of algorithmic problem. Therefore, the paper could also fit into cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also discusses tree grammars, which are a type of formal grammar, and the use of tree automata, which are a type of automaton. These topics could fit into cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
